    {
      "id": "scenario_2b3_s2",
      "name": "Service Side Electrical Fault",
      "description": "Both circuits are running with heat transfer active, but the service motor fuse F_Service has just tripped. M_Service is de-energised; the shaft is stationary so P_Service has stopped automatically. Respond: open SW_P_Iso to stop M_Process — P_Process auto-stops when the shaft stops — then close V_P1 to isolate the process side. Open SW_S_Iso, reset F_Service, close SW_S_Iso — M_Service auto-restarts and P_Service auto-restarts. Open V_P1, then close SW_P_Iso — M_Process auto-restarts and P_Process auto-restarts.",
