    {
      "id": "scenario_2b3_s3",
      "name": "Controlled Dual Shutdown",
      "description": "Both circuits are running with full heat transfer. Shut down safely in the correct order — process first, then service (the cooling side stays running until the process side is isolated): open SW_P_Iso to stop M_Process — P_Process auto-stops when the shaft stops — then close V_P2 → de-energise PS_Process. Then open SW_S_Iso to stop M_Service — P_Service auto-stops — then close V_S2 → de-energise PS_Service. Closing a discharge valve while the pump shaft is still turning will dead-head the pump.",
      "difficulty": "hard",
